Odana Area Plan: Meeting of May 27, 2021
description: Draft land use, transportation, parks and open space, and maximum height maps for the Odana Area Plan were shared in late January.  Project staff have made some edits since that time, and are looking forward to sharing updated concepts at two virtual meetings: an Evening Engagement on May 27th at 5:30pm, and a Lunch & Learn on June 1st at 12:00 p.m. (noon).  The same information will be presented at both meetings, and one, possibly both, of the meetings will be recorded.  In addition to updated maps, potential proactive rezoning of properties and possible official mapping of planned street connections will be summarized.

South Madison Plan Strategies and Recommendations - Meeting of April 15, 2021
description:
The South Madison planning team has been working on an update to the South Madison Neighborhood Plan adopted in 2005. However due to COVID-19, as well as the uprisings and calls for systemic change, the plan took a pause in late March 2020.

We intend to address and build on relevant issues identified by the South Madison community through an action-oriented plan prioritizing community wealth building, anti-displacement and gentrification, and opportunities to thrive. We invite all South Madison residents, business owners and other stakeholders to participate in a conversation about the draft South Madison Plan strategies and recommendations. 

The City of Madison is dedicated to ensuring that all residents have a voice in processes that affect them. Please help us make this happen by taking a minute to fill out this optional survey. All responses are private and will only be used in aggregate and not reported out individually.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/madison_meeting_demographics
